 style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">protocol<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Prepare a sample of the cells by washing them in the final desired media by centrifugation. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> , removal of old media and addition of new media.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"C18234A07B2E11EB904F4F4F1ADA96F9","order_id":2,"type_id":30,"title":"centrifuge","source":{"centrifuge":"3000","duration":180,"error_centrifuge":false,"error_temperature":false,"guid":"C18234A07B2E11EB904F4F4F1ADA96F9","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"scientificNotation":{"centrifuge":false,"temperature":false},"start":null,"temperature":"25","temperatureUnit":10,"unit":34}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1136624,"guid":"EBB19D107B2E11EB904F4F4F1ADA96F9","previous_id":1136622,"previous_guid":"D8167FB07B2D11EB904F4F4F1ADA96F9","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"38A12A82D77742C0A82F9EB2F9606172","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Glass slide preparation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B2E3E6842CC64006B5F6D666FE762797","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">In glass slide, attach the Frame-seal Slide chambers, 15x15, 65 \u03bcl. <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Add the sample<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Seal the chamber with a cover slip<\/li><\/ol><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1136625,"guid":"29D5D1107B2F11EB904F4F4F1ADA96F9","previous_id":1136624,"previous_guid":"EBB19D107B2E11EB904F4F4F1ADA96F9","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"F8833F60D76A4D4CB555FCA961AC9068","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Imaging"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"46208888C7384AE99D0E22490C181D4D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Set the glass slide in the microscope for image acquisition<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Record sequential images in a fixed interval (e.g. 100 ms per frame) using the desired laser\/filter settings. <\/li><\/ol><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1136633,"guid":"46863B107B3411EB904F4F4F1ADA96F9","previous_id":1136625,"previous_guid":"29D5D1107B2F11EB904F4F4F1ADA96F9","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"3B5F5070551441BF8C2477FC6226780B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Cell tracking analysis - imageJ"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"D4FBC6ACC650446BBBBAFEE33367E7C0","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Open the image file in imageJ<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Adjust brightness and contrast (Image -> Adjust -> Brightness\/Contrast -> auto)<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Open the Plugins -> Tracking -> TrackMate<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Check the image settings (eg. Size and pixels), next<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Choose the detector system, next<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Input the estimate size of cells and define a threshold, next<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">After detection, choose a range of spots quality, next<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Select a view option, next<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Set filter in spots, next<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Define the maximum linking distance between frames, next<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Set color for tracks, next<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Open analysis and save the results in a csv file<\/li><\/ol><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">*The analysis files contains information about the tracks, as average speed, max speed, position, etc. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">** A video demonstrating the TrackMate workflow can be found <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=Rzz_eump4JQ&feature=youtu.be\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">here<\/span><\/a><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1136640,"guid":"C64BA9F07B3611EB904F4F4F1ADA96F9","previous_id":1136633,"previous_guid":"46863B107B3411EB904F4F4F1ADA96F9","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"34029474388B4FD58ADFD5EDA4544CBB","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Data analysis"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"0544D2A955A942A2AF9F7C901E3DEB42","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Analyse the data generated. For example, after organizing the data of each test in a excel tab, the R code below demonstrate a possible workflow and analysis to generate a density plot. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><pre><code><div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">library(dplyr)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">library(ggplot2)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">library(readxl)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">#set the working directory<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">wd <- setwd(\"D:\/Path\")<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">#Get all file names with .xlsx in the working folder.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">FileNames <- Sys.glob(\"*.xlsx\")<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">#load file with results<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">cc1690_1 <- read_excel(\"UZH20201206 Motility.xlsx\", sheet = \"1690_1\")<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">cc1690_2 <- read_excel(\"UZH20201206 Motility.xlsx\", sheet = \"1690_2\")<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">cc1690_3 <- read_excel(\"UZH20201206 Motility.xlsx\", sheet = \"1690_3\")<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">cc1690 <- rbind(cc1690_1, cc1690_2, cc1690_3)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">MAW8_1 <- read_excel(\"UZH20201206 Motility.xlsx\", sheet = \"MAW8_1\")<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">MAW8_2 <- read_excel(\"UZH20201206 Motility.xlsx\", sheet = \"MAW8_2\")<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">MAW8_3 <- read_excel(\"UZH20201206 Motility.xlsx\", sheet = \"MAW8_3\")<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">MAW8 <- rbind(MAW8_1, MAW8_2, MAW8_3)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">GP1_1 <- read_excel(\"UZH20201206 Motility.xlsx\", sheet = \"GP1_1\")<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">GP1_2 <- read_excel(\"UZH20201206 Motility.xlsx\", sheet = \"GP1_2\")<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">GP1_3 <- read_excel(\"UZH20201206 Motility.xlsx\", sheet = \"GP1_3\")<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">GP1 <- rbind(GP1_1, GP1_2, GP1_3)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">#Take the last 10 seconds of the experiment<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">cc1690 <- filter(cc1690, start_t > 50)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">MAW8 <- filter(MAW8, start_t > 50)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">GP1 <- filter(GP1, start_t > 50)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">#Add column with Strain information<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">cc1690_n <- c(\"cc1690\")<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">cc1690 <- cbind(cc1690, strain = cc1690_n)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">MAW8_n <- c(\"MAW8\")<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">MAW8 <- cbind(MAW8, strain = MAW8_n)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">GP1_n <- c(\"GP1\")<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">GP1 <- cbind(GP1, strain = GP1_n)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">#Combine data<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">df <- rbind(cc1690, MAW8, GP1)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"># Convert data to speed um\/s (File recorder at 100ms\/frame|speed in frames\/s)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">df$speed_r <- df$speed*10<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">#generates the plot<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">myplot <- ggplot(df, aes(speed_r, fill=strain))+<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">  geom_density(alpha=0.4) + <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">  scale_fill_manual(limits = c(\"cc1690\",<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">                               \"MAW8\",<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">                               \"GP1\"),<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">                    values=c(\"#1b9e77\",<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">                             \"#d95f02\",<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">                             \"#7570b3\"))+<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">  theme(text=element_text(size=12, <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">                          #       family=\"Comic Sans MS\"))<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">                          #       family=\"CM Roman\"))<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">                          #       family=\"mono\"))<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">                          #       family=\"sans\"))<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">                          family=\"serif\",<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">                          face=\"bold\"),<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">        plot.background = element_blank(),<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">        panel.grid.major = element_blank(),<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">        panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">        panel.border = element_blank(),<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">        panel.background = element_rect(fill='white', colour='white'),<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">        axis.line = element_line(colour = \"black\", size = 0.6), #thickness axis<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">        axis.ticks = element_line(size=0.8), #thickness ticks<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">        axis.text.x = element_text(face=\"bold\", colour='black'),<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">        axis.text.y = element_text(face=\"bold\", colour='black'),<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">        legend.key=element_blank())+<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">  labs(x = (expression(paste(\"Speed (\",  #label x axis<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">                             mu, \"\/\", \"s\",<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">                             \")\", <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">                             sep=\"\"))), <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">       y = \"Density\")  #  Lavel y axis<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">#to save graph<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">ggsave(<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">  paste(\"motility\",\".png\"),<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">  myplot,<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">  width = 6.41,<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">  height = 3.73,<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">  dpi = 1200<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">)<\/div><\/div><\/code><\/pre><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA9F6C","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":"","materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>This protocols describe the steps required for the motility quantification in <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Chlamydomonas reinhardtii<\/span><span>.  <\/span><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1614676734}